<TITLE> Harassment caused girl to take poison, alleges family </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 3(bdnews24.com)A 14 year old girl, Umme Kulsum Elora, a student of class 8 at South Banasree Model High School, committed suicide because of constant teasing by a boy, according to the girl's mother. Her mother Halima Khatun told journalists at Dhaka Medical College Hospital (DMCH) that her daughter took poison on Saturday and died on the way to the hospital. Elora lived with her family in a rented house at 65, Madhya Nandipara. She was the youngest of four daughters and one son of Halima and Nizamuddin Mollah, a government employee "Elora was being disturbed by this boy called Rezaul for the last one year," her mother said. "She had been going to school in a school van, but because of the harassment, I started to take her to school and bring her back home. Elora even gave me her mobile phone about one month and a half ago because of the constant calls. Arbitration was sought between the boy's father Babr Ali and local elites. But it did not work out." Halima alleged that two days before she died, Rezaul wanted to talk to her daughter on her the way back from school. When Halima and Elora did not respond, he uttered threatening words to them. On Elora's return from school on Saturday, Halima recounted to the journalists, that she told her mother in the kitchen,"Ma, will you sleep with me for a bit". And as he said this, she fell down on the floor. On seeing froth on her daughter's lips, Halima took her to DMCH as quickly as she could, but Elora died on the way. Khilgaon thana OC Md Nizamuddin told bdnews24.com that the girls' father had come to the police station and "alleged that his daughter committed suicide due to teasing by Rezaul." He said that a case had been filed against the boy.. B
